timeline.bodyText:
Just asking:
Wouldn't it be possible to define the state machine once in a lifecycle processor.
Currently you need to check whether the transition is OK and also you always need to take the transition in the elementTypeProcessor implementations. But this lifecycle is always the same right?
Could look like this:
LifecycleProcessor {

 if (elementType == Activating)
{
  processors.get(elementType).onActivating(context)
  transitionToActivated()
}
else if (elementType == Completing)
{
  processors.get(elementType).onCompleting(context)
  transitionToCompleted()
}
}

